parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and rusting of brake lines can cause sudden brake failure, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal goes to the floor
loss of braking power
ABS warning light illuminates
and unusual noises when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ABS system can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Unusual noises when braking
ABS warning light illuminates
brake pedal pulsates or vibrates
and loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
and loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unintentionally, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The parking brake pedal goes to the floor
the parking brake does not hold the vehicle in drive
neutral
or reverse
the parking brake shoes wear down prematurely
the parking brake cable is not connected
and the parking brake actuator lever is missing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants of the vehicle are not protected from the impact.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
even when the crash is severe enough to warrant deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of side airbags to deploy in a side impact can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants of the vehicle are not protected from the impact.
symptoms: Side airbags do not deploy in a side impact
even when the impact is severe enough to warrant deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Failure Due to Sensor Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbag sensors to detect a crash can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy, resulting in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
even when the crash is severe enough to warrant deployment
due to a malfunction of the airbag sensors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of seatbelts to retract or function properly can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants of the vehicle are not properly restrained.
symptoms: Seatbelts do not retract or function properly
leading to difficulties in securing occupants in the vehicle.
